  "title": "Accountant (Construction Industry) | Tampines | Up to $5,500 + AWS + VB",
  "description": "<h3><strong>About the Company</strong></h3>\n<p>Our client is a <strong>reputable construction and engineering firm</strong> headquartered in <strong>China</strong> and <strong>listed on NASDAQ</strong>. With established operations in Singapore, the company manages diverse infrastructure and development projects. They are seeking a capable <strong>Accountant</strong> to join their local finance team and support continued growth in the region.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>📍 <strong>Location:</strong> Tampines<br>\n🕒 <strong>Working Hours:</strong> Monday – Friday, 9:00 AM – 6:00 PM<br>\n🎁 <strong>Benefits:</strong> 13th Month AWS, Annual Bonus, 14 Days Annual Leave</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<h3><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Handle full set of accounts including AP, AR, GL, and month-end closing.</li>\n  <li>Prepare financial statements, management reports, and consolidation reports.</li>\n  <li>Manage statutory reporting, GST submission, and corporate tax compliance.</li>\n  <li>Ensure proper internal controls and compliance with accounting standards.</li>\n  <li>Conduct financial analysis, cost monitoring, and profitability reporting.</li>\n  <li>Assist in budgeting, forecasting, and audit preparation.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with auditors, tax agents, and HQ on accounting matters.</li>\n  <li>Perform other ad-hoc duties assigned by the Finance Director.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s Degree in Accountancy, Finance, or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>At least 3 years of relevant experience in full set accounting, tax, and consolidation.</li>\n  <li><strong>Experience in construction industry is a must.</strong></li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of Singapore accounting and tax regulations.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in Microsoft Excel and accounting software (e.g. Dynamics 365, NetSuite).</li>\n  <li>Bilingual in English and Mandarin (to liaise with HQ).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>EA License No: 23C1703 </p>\n<p>EA Personnel No: R1762582 </p>\n<p>EA Personnel Name: Wong Choo Sian, Jabez</p>\n<p><br></p>",
